  "claim_short": "2506.09324 Position of L(X,Y) in Lip_0(X,Y) Question 1.1 separable domain all codomains projection. If the scalar Lipschitz-free barycenter beta_X:F(X)->X has a bounded linear right inverse, then L(X,Y) is complemented in Lip_0(X,Y) for every Banach codomain Y. Key observation F_Y(X) is canonically isometric to scalar F(X). By Godefroy-Kalton lifting theorem, every separable X has norm-one right inverse, so L(X,Y)...",
